 We specialize in designing, developing, implementing, and supporting integrated advanced technology systems to address complex business challenges. Our proprietary technologies incorporate artificial intelligence applications, including video analytics-based security applications, intelligent process controls, and information technologies for a wide range of global customers. For more information, please visit our website at http://www.duostech.com/. 
 We are seeking to fill the position of Linux Administrator. This is a full-time, Exempt position located at our corporate headquarters in Jacksonville, FL and reports to the Vice President of Information Technology. 
 The Linux Administrator is responsible for installation, configuration and maintenance of Linux systems (Debian and Redhat based) and build and create scripts for automated deployment and configuration of Linux platforms using our RMM platform. The Linux Administrator must understand how interoperability is done with Linux and Windows platforms and contribute to overall design and configuration methods. In addition, serve as the primary escalation resource for all Linux systems internally and externally for issues that cannot be resolved at the Tier I and II levels. 
 Responsibilities and Duties: 
 Developing shell scripts for automation of maintenance and configuration. 
 Ubuntu Server configuration for new deployments. 
 Configuring procedures in Kaseya RMM platform. 
 Monitoring system patches and updating when needed. 
 Building and maintaining Linux machines in VSphere. 
 Documentation of all configurations and licensing used. 
 Configuring authentication for Linux system via Azure/AD. 
 Tier3 escalation resource for Linux based systems. 
 Qualifications and Skills: 
 Proven work experience using Linux platform 
 Able to multi-task 
 At least 5 years of experience as a Linux Systems Administrator 
 Strong understanding of TCP/IP 
 VMWare Experience 
 Excellent Documentation and Organization Skills 
 LPIC or Linux+ are preferred 
 Windows Server Administration Experience are preferred 
 Azure Administration Experience are preferred 
 Problem Solver 
 Positive Team Player 
